{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀγορά</b> [ᾰγ], ᾶς, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> ἀγορή, ῆς, ἡ, (ἀγείρω):— <b>assembly</b>, especially <b>of the People</b>, opposed to the Council of Chiefs, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.93, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.69, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τοῖσιν δ᾽ οὔτ᾽ ἀγοραὶ βουληφόροι (i.e. Κυκλώπεσσι) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.112; ὀρθῶν ἑσταότων ἀ γένετ᾽ οὐδέ τις ἔτλη ἕζεσθαι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.246\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. Πυλάτιδες, of the <b>Amphictyonic Council</b> at Pylae, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 638, cf. Ion Eleg. 1.3; μακάρων ἀ. 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 8(7).29, compare “Anecdota Graeca - Bekker” 210\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀγορήνδε καλέσσασθαι, κηρύσσειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.54, 2.51\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀγορὴν ποιήσασθαι, θέσθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.489, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.171\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; εἰς ἀ. ἰέναι, ἀγέρεσθαι,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8.12, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.245; ἀγορήνδε καθέζεσθαι 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.372.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]—Not common in Prose, ἀγορὰν συνάγειν, συλλέγειν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.7.3; ποιῆσαι 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.27; ἀγορὰς ποιεῖσθαι 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “Fragmenta” 150\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: of the assembly in Attic demes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 44.36, “IG” 2.585, +others; ἀ. συνέδριον φυλετῶν καὶ δημοτῶν “Anecdota Graeca - Bekker” 327: in late Prose, ἀ. δικῶν προθεῖναι, καταστήσασθαι\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], = Latin <i>conventus agere</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]“Bis Acc.” 4,12: <b>meeting for games</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 3.14: _metaphorically_, μυρμήκων ἀ. 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Icar.” 19: proverbial, θεῶν ἀ. 'Babel', 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>place of assembly</b>, τοὺς δ᾽ εὗρ᾽ εἰν ἀγορῇ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 7.382; ἵνα σφ᾽ ἀ. τε θέμις τε 11.807, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.266; _plural_, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.16; οὔτε.. εἰς ἀ. ἔρχεται οὔτε δίκας 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 268. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>market-place</b>, perhaps not earlier than [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Hom.epigram” 14.5 πολλὰ μὲν εἰν ἀγορῇ πωλεύμενα, πολλὰ δ᾽ ἀγυιαῖς\">Refs</a>]; frequently in later authors, πρυμνοῖς ἀγορᾶς ἔπι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 5.93; θεοὶ.. ἀγορᾶς ἐπίσκοποι 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 272; μέση Τραχινίων ἀ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 424; ἀγορᾷ οὐδὲ ἄστει δέχεσθαι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.44; ὀλιγάκις.. ἀγορᾶς χραίνων κύκλον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 919\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ ἐκ τῆς ἀ. <b>market</b> people, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.2.18; ἐξ ἀγορᾶς εἶ 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 181, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εἰς ἀ. ἐμβάλλειν to go into <b>the forum</b>, i. e. be a citizen, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 5\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν τῇ ἀ. ἐργάζεσθαι to trade in <b>the market</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 57.31\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; εἰς τὴν ἀ. χειροτονεῖν (opposed to ἐπὶ τὸν πόλεμον) 'for <b>the market'</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 4.26; the Roman “Forum”, 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 5.48. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>business of the</b> ἀγορά: <br /><Level3><b>__III.1</b></Level3> <b>public speaking, gift of speaking</b>, mostly in <i>plural</i>, ἔσχ᾽ ἀγοράων withheld him <b>from speaking</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.275\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ δ᾽ ἀγορὰς ἀγόρευον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 788, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.818; ᾠδὴν ἀντ᾽ ἀγορῆς θέμενος 6th c.BC: Solon Lyricus 1. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>market</b>, ἀγορὰν παρασκευάζειν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.40, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 3.4.11; ἀ. παρέχειν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.44, etc.; ἄγειν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.7.33, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to ἀγορᾷ χρῆσθαι to have <b>supplies</b>,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 7.6.24; τῆς ἀ. εἴργεσθαι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.67, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pericles” 29\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. ἐλευθέρα, i. e. καθαρὰ τῶν ὠνίων πάντων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1331a31, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.2.3; opposed to ἀ. ἀναγκαία 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1331b11\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; generally, <b>provisions, supplies,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PPetr. 3p.131 (3rd c.BC), “PS” 14.354 (3rd c.BC), +others\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; in <i>plural</i>, Nic.Dam.p.6.17 [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἀγορὰς περικόπτειν cut off <b>supplies</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 10.43. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.2.b</b></Level4> <b>market, sale</b>, ἀ. τῶν βιβλίων, τῶν παρθένων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Ind.” 19, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Varia Historia” 4.1, compare 4th c.BC: Nicochares Comicus 7. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> as a mark of time, ἀ. πλήθουσα <b>the forenoon</b>, when the market-place was full, ἀγορῆς πληθυούσης[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.181; πληθούσης ἀγορᾶς 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.1.10, compare “SIG” 695.38 (5th c.BC: Magnes Comicus Mae.)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; περὶ or ἀμφὶ ἀ. πλήθουσαν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.1.7, 1.8.1; ἐν ἀ. πληθούσῃ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 469d, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.92; also ἀγορῆς πληθώρη 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.173, 7.223; poetry, ἐν ἀ. πλήθοντος ὄχλου 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.85; πρὶν ἀ. πεπληθέναι 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 29: ἀγορῆς διάλυσις\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>the time just after mid-day</b>, when they went home from market, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.104, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 12.1. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> <b>marketday</b>, = Latin <i>nundinae</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 7.58.\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0058","accentedUnicode":"ἀγορά","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0059","matchingForm":"ἀγοράζω","stepTransliteration":"agorazō","gloss":"to buy","_zh_tw_Gloss":"買","_es_Gloss":"comprar","_zh_Gloss":"买"},{"strongNumber":"G0060","matchingForm":"ἀγοραῖος","stepTransliteration":"agoraios","gloss":"of the marketplace","_zh_tw_Gloss":"市集","_es_Gloss":"del mercado","_zh_Gloss":"市集"},{"strongNumber":"G1453","matchingForm":"ἐγείρω","stepTransliteration":"egeirō","gloss":"to arise","_zh_tw_Gloss":"復活, 起來","_es_Gloss":"levantarse ","_zh_Gloss":"复活, 起来"}],"shortDef":"marketplace (as a center of social and commercial life)","mediumDef":"marketplace (as a center of social and commercial life) <br /><b>a place of public concourse, forum, market-place; things said in the market, provision</b>","stepGloss":"marketplace","stepTransliteration":"agora","count":11,"_es_Definition":"mercado plaza","_zh_tw_Definition":"市集","_zh_Definition":"市集","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"nơi nhóm chợ; quảng trường – Agora là nơi lộ thiên để hội họp ở các thành bang Hy Lạp thời cổ xưa.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"街市","_es_Gloss":"mercado","_zh_Gloss":"街市"}]}